By Esther Egbe
Former Super Eagles striker and FC  Dynamo Moscow player said that he is not interested in playing for the  National Team anytime soon because of the way he was treated,National Daily learnt.
He urged that things should change and players invitation be given without sentiment.
National Daily gathered that Sly as he is fondly called said it was the suggestion of his coach to move him down to the feeder team when he arrived FC Midtjyland from FC Ebedei, ” we were three that came from Nigeria, but the coaches advised that I stepdown  to team B, I listened to him and the advice paid off as I later became a better player scoring goals in Denmark.
Igboun  confirmed that he will never go into coaching in future because of his lifestyle which doesn’t fit the noble profession.